## How It Works

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Frontend
    participant Backend
    participant DB
    participant Disk

    User->>Frontend: Type message + attach files
    Frontend->>Backend: POST /api/chat/send (FormData)
    Backend->>DB: INSERT chat_messages → get message_id
    loop Each file
        Backend->>Backend: Validate extension
        Backend->>Disk: Save to uploads/chat_attachments/{uuid}_{name}
        Backend->>DB: INSERT chat_attachments (linked by message_id)
    end
    Backend->>Frontend: { message, attachments[] }
    Frontend->>User: Show message in chat
```

## What's NOT Changed

- All existing endpoints (`POST /sessions`, `GET /sessions/{user_id}`, `GET /sessions/{id}/messages`, `POST /sessions/{id}/messages`) remain intact
- Bot mock-response still uses the old JSON endpoint (bots don't have attachments)
- No RAG or vector DB integration
- Suggestion buttons still work (they pass no files, which defaults to `[]`)

## Verification

- Backend should auto-reload with uvicorn (if it doesn't, restart with `uvicorn app.main:app --reload`)
- Frontend auto-reloads with Next.js dev server
- Test by clicking the paperclip icon, selecting files, and sending a message
- Files will appear in `backend/uploads/chat_attachments/`
- Check `chat_attachments` table in PostgreSQL for new records
